Ask HN: Resources for Android HAL, Framework, Platform Development in Automotive
text: Basically the title. I work in an IT company as an android application developer for automotive infotainment systems. So far my work has been in limited to android coding for making HMI interface and the android service layer related to the apps. I have some expertise in IPC communication implementation using AIDL, between the apps inside the custom automotive OS we develop. I want to have a good understanding of android native frameworks and services and android HAL layer. Also would like to have some exposure to concepts of JNI and to have experience in interfacing JAVA and native layer modules through JNI. If anyone knows good resources to start at these things in light of automotive domain, please share it with me. If you can guide me in the right direction, advices are also helpful to someone who is aspired to have a career in this automotive platform development. I would like to switch for a job where these skills are required, but my android application development knowledge is not enough to crack any of those interviews that seek knowledge and experience in automotive platform development. Thanks in Advance!

Show HN: TinyMCE and PouchDB Text App
text:
This simple text app uses an older version of TinyMCE and one of their older demos.

I also use Bootstrap, jQuery, and some add ons to both to both of those.

It lets you create "Folders" (PouchDBs) to store and manage documents. You can CRUD and search for documents.

It's pretty easy to configure it to use a web based CouchDB for multiple users to create and manage documents from anywhere.

There's also a zip file of the app you can download at https://cherrypc.com/textapp.zip

You don't need a webserver to use it. Just load the index.html file from the textapp folder.
